snippet: A high court judge ruled that the $16 million London mansion bought by Saadi Qaddafi was bought with stolen Libyan government funds.
abstract: Libyan governemnt is granted possession of $16 million London mansion bought by Saadi Qaddafi, son of former Libyan leader Col Muammar el-Qaddafi, with what high court judge rules were stolen Libyan government funds.
lead_paragraph: A high court judge ruled that the $16 million London mansion bought by Saadi Qaddafi was bought with stolen Libyan government funds.

headline.main: Britain: Court Hands Qaddafi Son’s Mansion to Libya
